    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="636"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7741a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-24T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 24, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>125. Department has received from the War Department message of January 22
                    containing your comments on the last paragraph of the President’s message as
                    sent to you on January 20 as Department’s 108. Your comments were most helpful
                    and are fully appreciated. In the light thereof you are authorized to substitute
                    for the last paragraph in the message the following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Furthermore, since you say that your Government is not in a position to
                            continue any direct maintenance of American troops in China, this
                            Government, in order to cover all of its military expenditures in China,
                            including such maintenance as well as construction, is prepared to place
                            to your account the U. S. dollar equivalent of any Chinese funds made
                            available under general arrangements that will be suggested by General
                            Stilwell and the Ambassador.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
